The article is a declaration by the Heads of State and Government of the nations contributing to the UN-mandated, NATO-led International Security Assistance Force (ISAF) in Afghanistan. The declaration reaffirms their commitment to Afghanistan's security and stability and recognizes the progress that has been made in transitioning to Afghan security responsibility. They express support for President Karzai's objective for the Afghan National Security Forces to lead security operations in all provinces by the end of 2014. The declaration emphasizes the importance of a comprehensive approach involving both civilian and military actors in achieving success in Afghanistan. They also discuss the process of transition, which will be conditions-based and will not equate to a withdrawal of ISAF troops. The article highlights the efforts being made to improve security, governance, and regional cooperation in Afghanistan. The declaration concludes by expressing a shared vision for a better future for Afghanistan and a commitment to seeing the mission through.